    {
      "id": "938891312636406",
      "score": 5,
      "review_title": "nice",
      "review_description": "After a few times of tests, I feel ready to give a fairly detailed review. What surprised me most about this game is the brilliant balance it strikes between “chaos” and “polish.” The combat system seems straightforward, but it hides impressive depth. Take the grapple, for example—it’s not just a movement tool, but a tactical core. You can use it to close distance, escape danger, seize high-ground advantage. The map design also deserves praise. Though maps aren’t huge, vertical space is used exceptionally well. Jump pads aren’t just for getting around—they’re pace-setters for combat. Weapon and item balance is generally good, though there’s room for tuning. Currently, the poison smoke grenade + slow mine combo feels overly dominant in tight spaces, almost creating “guaranteed kill zones.” I’d suggest adding some counterplay—maybe certain skills or items can temporarily clear smoke, or wearing specific gear reduces slowdown effects, to encourage more diverse counter-strategies.",
      "date": 1766132576,
      "review_helpful_count": 31,
      "author_display_name": "czp1220157987",
      "author_alias": "czp1220157987",
      "developer_response": null
    },
